FT  24 SEP 94 / World News in Brief: Footsie ends nervous week steadier
The UK stock market ended a difficult week on a firmer note with the help of
an improvement in the stock index futures and bond sectors, although trading
volume remained unimpressive. In early trade, the FT-SE 100 Index plunged 22
points through the 3,000 mark to 2,999.2, but recovered to 3,028.2 at the
close, a net gain of 7 points. The Footsie fell by just over 1 per cent on
the week. London stocks, Page 17
